div.bibl: THE PHILIPPINE MESSENGER Vol. III, No. 3, Jan. 26, 1936 "Phi Alpha Gamma Rizal Day"

body.p: Miss Emmy Gyinto, a young lady of 15, who attends the McKinley High School, was the Rizal Day Queen of the Phi Alpha Gamma, held at the International House, Dec. 28, 1936. Her sister, May, who is only 4 years old, has a wonderful voice. The little lady will entertain the guests. Miss Emmy and her family reside at 1619 Warren Blvd.

Miss Luordes Bolloso, a charming Pinay (Filipino) and nurse at Columbus Hospital, sang a number of songs in Tagalog (Filipino Language) and in English. She was accompanied by a young Filipino guitarist. The affair was more or less very formal.
